The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent TODAY is a special day for singer, actor, comedian and dancer Madlela Skhobokhobo as he has turned 41. The artiste who was born in Nkayi and grew up in Gwanda has over the past two decades been entertaining people from rural Gwanda to venues across the Limpopo. <img class="wp-image-528065 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Madlela-final.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Madlela-final.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Madlela-final-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Madlela Skhobokhobo Mostly known for his axe-wielding stint, Madlela has become a darling to many though his hilarious skits, educative dramas and music. From the Chronicle Showbiz team, we say happy 41st birthday Dlelas, khula uze ukhokobe Jahunda leNkayi. Always remember that a dream never dies. â€“ @mthabisi_mthire